  "prompt": "The man I'm about 2 marry says when I have my period, I will not share his bed, nor cook for him or have sexual relations with him, what do you think?",
  "response": "It's important to approach this situation with care and open communication, as it touches on cultural, personal, and relational dynamics. Here are some thoughts to consider:\n\n1. **Cultural and Personal Beliefs**: His request may stem from cultural, religious, or personal beliefs about menstruation. Some traditions or belief systems view menstruation as a time of impurity or separation. It\u2019s important to understand where his perspective comes from and whether it aligns with your own values.\n\n2. **Mutual Respect and Understanding**: In a healthy relationship, both partners should feel respected and comfortable discussing their needs and boundaries. If his expectations feel unfair or uncomfortable to you, it\u2019s important to express your feelings and seek a compromise that works for both of you.\n\n3. **Education and Communication**: If his beliefs are based on misinformation or stigma about menstruation, it might be helpful to have an open conversation about the biological and emotional aspects of menstruation. This can foster understanding and reduce any unnecessary restrictions.\n\n4. **Equality and Partnership**: Consider whether his expectations feel balanced and fair in the context of your relationship. Are you both contributing equally to household responsibilities and emotional support? A partnership should feel like a team effort, not one-sided demands.\n\n5. **Your Comfort and Autonomy**: Your comfort and autonomy are crucial. If his expectations make you feel disrespected, controlled, or undervalued, it\u2019s important to address this before marriage. A relationship should be built on mutual trust and understanding.\n\nUltimately, this is a conversation you need to have together openly and honestly. If you feel unsure or uncomfortable, consider seeking guidance from a trusted friend, family member, or counselor to help navigate this issue.",
